let _markdown = "\n\nThe following tools support installing and running Open Plugin plugins.\n\nClaude Code [#claude-code]\n\n[Claude Code](https://code.claude.com) is Anthropic's agentic coding tool. It supports plugins via the `--plugin-dir` flag for development and built-in plugin installation for distribution.\n\n**Supported components**: Skills, Agents, Rules, Hooks, MCP Servers\n\n```bash\n# Load a plugin during development\nclaude --plugin-dir ./my-plugin\n\n# Invoke a plugin skill\n/my-plugin:hello\n```\n\nCursor [#cursor]\n\n[Cursor](https://cursor.com) is an AI-powered code editor. It supports Open Plugin for extending its agent capabilities with custom skills, rules, and tool servers.\n\n**Supported components**: Skills, Rules, MCP Servers\n\nAdding support [#adding-support]\n\nOpen Plugin is designed for incremental adoption. A tool only needs to support one component type to be conformant. See [Integrate Plugins](/agent-builders) for a step-by-step guide to adding plugin support to your tool.\n";
